description: Numbers with multiplicative digital root value 0.
comments: Numbers with root value 1 are the 'repunits' (see A000042).This sequence has density 1. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Apr 01 2009Any integer with at least one 0 among its base 10 digits is in this sequence. - _Alonso del Arte_, Aug 29 2014
links: Franklin T. Adams-Watters, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..10000
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Multiplicative Digital Root
example: 20 is in the sequence because 2 * 0 = 0.25 is in the sequence because 2 * 5 = 10 and 1 * 0 = 0.
crossrefs: Cf. A034048, A002275, A034049, A034050, A034051, A034052, A034053, A034054, A034055, A034056 (numbers having multiplicative digital roots 0-9).
Cf. the subsets A011540 and A008592.
author: _Patrick De Geest_, Sep 15 1998.
